Introduction

NND, short for Night N Day, was a South Korean male duo formed by TAKEIL. The group officially debuted on March 16, 2024, with their first EP Wonder, I. The duo consisted of members Dayn and YoungJun, both of whom participated in the songwriting process of the album. Their name symbolized an ambition to create music that could be enjoyed at any time, both night and day.

NND first appeared on March 2, 2024, when TAKEIL launched the group’s official social media accounts. A debut showcase was held at Lim Arts Center in Gangnam on March 15, followed by the EP release the next day. Prior to the debut, the group released a demo version of their title track "Overdrive" on March 9, drawing attention for its polished sound and emotional tone.

In July 2024, TAKEIL announced NND’s first European tour scheduled for November, but the tour was cancelled in October due to internal circumstances. Following a period of inactivity and the tour’s cancellation, the group is believed to have quietly disbanded by the end of 2024.

After the disbandment, YoungJun signed with Way Better under the stage name YYJ in February 2025. The current status of Dayn remains unknown.
